"""_2_Comparaion_or_Relational"""

'''

Python Comparison (Relational) Operators:
=========================================
| ------------ | --------------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------ | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Operator     | Name                  | Purpose (Simple Meaning)        | Mathematical Analogy     | Python Example     | Output     | Real-World Use Case                                |
| ------------ | --------------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------ | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `==`         | Equal To              | Checks if both values are same  | 7 = 7                    | `5 == 5`           | `True`     | Login match, OTP validation, data comparison       |
| `!=`         | Not Equal To          | Checks if values differ         | 5 ≠ 2                    | `9 != 4`           | `True`     | Filter mismatches, error checks, anomaly detection |
| `<`          | Less Than             | Checks if left value is smaller | 5 < 8 → True             | `10 < 20`          | `True`     | Age check, discount eligibility, minimum criteria  |
| `<=`         | Less Than or Equal    | Checks smaller or equal         | 6 ≤ 6 → True             | `15 <= 15`         | `True`     | Upper limits, boundary checks                      |
| `>`          | Greater Than          | Checks if left value is larger  | 9 > 3 → True             | `25 > 10`          | `True`     | Performance check, salary comparison               |
| `>=`         | Greater Than or Equal | Checks larger or equal          | 12 ≥ 11 → True           | `7 >= 3`           | `True`     | Threshold checks, pass marks validation            |
| ------------ | --------------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------ | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------- |

'''